value.value: Adult intrinsic neuron with bilateral arbors in multiple VNC neuromeres (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It is a secondary neuron of the 19A hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in the T2 leg neuropil and sends output to the leg neuropil (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 4 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the mesothoracic neuromere and metathoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
